# Environment variables for Android (Capacitor) debug/validation builds.
#
# Copy this file to .env.android (git-ignored, never commit it) and fill in
# real values, then build with:
#   npm run build:android
#   npx cap sync android
#
# Native Android push also requires a Firebase google-services.json at
# android/app/google-services.json; see docs/android-firebase-configuration.md.
#
# Why this file exists:
# The Capacitor Android WebView loads the app at https://localhost (an
# HTTPS origin) in every build variant, including debug. VITE_API_URL here
# MUST therefore be an HTTPS backend. A plain http:// address - including a
# developer machine's LAN IP - will be blocked by the WebView's Mixed
# Content policy regardless of backend CORS configuration, and must never
# be committed here. See docs/android-api-configuration.md for details.
#
# VITE_API_URL below is the real, permanent, live production backend
# (confirmed reachable and confirmed to allow the https://localhost origin
# via CORS as of ISSUE-207). There is currently no separately-deployed
# staging backend live (the staging URL referenced in
# frontend/.env.staging.example does not resolve to an active deployment).
# Prefer a dedicated staging backend for routine Android development once
# one exists, to avoid mixing test usage with real production data; until
# then, be mindful that this target is production and avoid creating or
# submitting throwaway test data (e.g. field/game submissions) against it.

VITE_API_URL=https://yeshmishak-production.up.railway.app

# Google OAuth Web application client ID used as Credential Manager's server
# client ID. It must exactly match the backend GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID audience.
# Never use an Android OAuth client ID here. Register a separate Android OAuth
# client for every application package/signing SHA-1 pair used for Android.
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_VAPID_KEY=
